e’ + <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, superseding the native Old English form, <i>Wealdhere</i>. It was a very popular name in medieval England, normally pronounced ‘Water’."],"variants":[{"name":"Walther","meanings":["from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i> ‘army’; name of the famous medieval minnesinger  Walther von der Vogelweide  (  <i>c.</i>1170– <i>c.</i>1230 )."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":21,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Walter de Bayley was born in 1238, in Clitheroe, Lancashire, England as the son of Otto de Mitton 'de Bayley' and Anota de Clitherow. He had at least 1 son with Hamiria or Ameriade Bayley. He died in 1261, in Clitheroe, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 23."},"et":{"1238–1261":"1238–1261","–Male":"Surnud","1240–Female":"1240–Surnud","1260–1290":"1260–1290","1210–Male":"1210–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","about 1260":"umbes 1260","1238":"1238","1259":"1259","1210":"1210","1240":"1240","1261":"1261","1260":"1260","1290":"1290","Clitheroe, Lancashire, England":"Clitheroe, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Stonyhurst, Clitheroe, Lancashire, England":"Clitheroe, Lancashire, England"},"fi":{"1238–1261":"1238–1261","–Male":"Kuollut","1240–Female":"1240–Kuollut","1260–1290":"1260–1290","1210–Male":"1210–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","about 1260":"noin 1260","1238":"1238","1259":"1259","1210":"1210","1240":"1240","1261":"1261","1260":"1260","1290":"1290","Clitheroe, Lancashire, England":"Clitheroe, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Stonyhurst, Clitheroe, Lancashire, England":"Clitheroe, Lancashire, Englan